    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10781</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Haitian Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ménos</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to announce
                    officially to Your Excellency that the Council of State of the Republic of
                    Haiti, exercising the legislative power by virtue of the Constitution in force,
                    has declared, on the report of the Executive branch, that a state of war exists
                    between the Republic of Haiti and the Empire of Germany as from July 12
                    instant.</p>
                <p>This decision, called forth by the aggressive and offensive attitude of the
                    Imperial German Government toward the Haitian Nation, <pb facs="0801" n="709"
                        xml:id="pg_709"/> implies at the same time a full indorsement by my
                    Government of the noble views which the President of the United States
                    expressed, notably in his memorable address of July 4.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d672fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_268">p. 268</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I take pleasure [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Solon Ménos</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
